SED command for 
1. searching
2. find
3. replace
4. insertion
5. deletion

Editing the file without opening them. 
1. Powerful textStream editor, 
2. Perform complex pattern matching

Commands and variation in it:
1. sed 's/<old-string>/<new-string>/' <file-name>  :  only replaces the 1st occurence of the string.
2. sed 's/<old-string>/<new-string>/k' <file-name>  : only replaces the kth occurence of the word.
3. sed 's/<old-string>/<new-string>/g' <file-name>  : replaces all the occurences of the string in the file.
4. sed 's/<old-string>/<new-string>/kg' <file-name>  : replaces all the occurences of the string in the file from kth.
5. sed 'ks/<old-string>/<new-string>g' <file-name>  : replaces the old string with the new string in kth line.
6. sed 's/<old-string>//g' <file-name> : removes the string.

